{
  "text": "Perceived ease of use, on the other hand, is constrained by perceptions about computer self-efficacy (i.e., belief that one has the skill to use the tool), external control (i.e., belief that an individual has institutional support to use the tool), computer anxiety (i.e., fear of using computers/technology), computer playfulness (i.e., cognitive spontaneity in microcomputer interactions), perceived enjoyment (i.e., enjoyment in using the tool), and objective usability (Marikyan & Papagiannidis 2023).",
  "mask": "(Marikyan & Papagiannidis 2023)",
